section.section:
Of the 13 Board members:
Four shall be licensed as clinical professional counselors;
Three shall be licensed as clinical marriage and family therapists;
Three shall be licensed as clinical alcohol and drug counselors;
One shall be licensed as a clinical professional art therapist; and
Two shall be consumer members.

text.section:
The consumer members of the Board:
Shall be members of the general public;
May not be or ever have been certified or licensed as a counselor or therapist or in training to become certified or licensed as a counselor or therapist;
May not have a household member who is certified or licensed as a counselor or therapist or in training to become certified or licensed as a counselor or therapist;
May not participate or ever have participated in a commercial or professional field related to professional counseling, marriage and family therapy, alcohol and drug counseling, or professional art therapy;
May not have a household member who participates in a commercial or professional field related to professional counseling, marriage and family therapy, alcohol and drug counseling, or professional art therapy;
May not have had within 2 years before appointment a substantial financial interest in a person regulated by the Board; and
While members of the Board, may not have a substantial financial interest in a person regulated by the Board.
